      "type": "lyric",
      "title": "Sun coming through the blinds",
      "content": "Sun coming through the blinds at seven\nMakes a ladder on the floor\nI've been lying here since heaven\nKnows what time, an hour or more\n\nThere's a word for what I'm feeling\nBut it lives behind my teeth\nSo I let the light keep dealing\nWith the things that I can't reach",
      "audiofile": "",
      "lyricfile": "",
      "project": "a1b2c3d4",
      "tags": ["verse", "morning", "imagery"],
      "links": ["i3c4d5e6"],
